RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 45. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NORTHERN CHARMER unhurried in the early going to trail the field to mid-turn, split rivals in a long drive turning for home, found best stride late and surged at the wire to be up in time. TATUM'S JOURNEY sped off to a clear lead shortly from the gate, maintained that advantage to mid-stretch but could not hold off the late charge of the winner. KARATS KOUNT rated off the pace to the turn, rallied four wide to be well positioned in upper stretch but failed to gain ground down the lane. BETTE'SGOTANOTION broke a step slow to give the field several lengths early and made steady progress mounting a mild bid. DANZINGWITHROYALTY prompted the pace for a half mile and weakened in the stretch. DROPPED COLD flashed brief speed to stalk early on, dropped to the rear of the field in the turn and never proved a threat. FAST N FEARLESS stalked the pace to the top of the lane and faded.

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke slow, mild late bid

ENTRY.COMMENT: speed, clear lead, couldn't last, gamely

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 7 1/2F Turf CR: 90. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE AUGUST 20, 2022. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Minnesota Bred Claimin g Price $25,000. (If management deems it inadvisable to run this race on the turf, two-year-old races will be run at 6 and 1/2 furlongs and races for three-year-olds and up will be run at a distance of 1 mile on the main track.) (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LORING PARK patiently handled while settled in hand into the first turn, rallied three wide in the final bend to engage the leaders in upper stretch and kicked clear down the lane. HOT SHOT KID reserved off the pace while racing along the fence down the backside, responded when called upon turning for home while angling out to the five path and closed well down the stretch. BARNFIELD slow early to trail the main pack by open lengths, was set to a drive in mid-turn, swung out wide in upper stretch and mounted a good belated rally. I'M NOBLE pressed the pace into the far turn to loom large at the head of the lane and flattened out in the drive. CARMENOOTZ stalked the pace to the quarter pole and failed to respond when called upon for the drive. BOARD CERTIFIED set the pace to upper stretch and weakened coming home.

ENTRY.COMMENT: speed, well rated, weakened late

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, well placed, no kick

ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, saved ground, angled wide, closed well

ENTRY.COMMENT: patient handling, rallied 3 wide, responded, kicked clear

ENTRY.NAME: I'm Noble
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, bid, flattened out,

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 85. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 28500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $12,500 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMI NG PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 20 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Claiming Races For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $40,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FREEBRITNEY slow early to be well off the rapid pace, gained ground to the pack in the turn, split horses five wide and closed with a rush to be up in the final strides. PRESENT TIME dueled on the pace through rapid fractions, battled on down the lane to be caught in deep stretch and came again in a determined drive only to be nailed at the wire by the winner. EMILY SMILES stalked the clear dueling leaders, rallied three wide at the top of the lane to engage the lead, fought through the lane to take a brief lead yards from the wire and was out-finished late in a game effort. SAINT SARENA sped off on the lead to duel through rapid fractions, responded when called upon for the drive while racing along the fence and was caught late in a good effort. LARIMAR chased the leaders through the turn, rallied while angling wide down the lane and idled in the final hundred yards. SAILING ALONG tracked the leaders while rushing up the fence for position down the backside and lacked a closing response when called upon for the drive. UNRIVALED QUEEN was never a serious threat.

ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside, no response
